HEADWORD: Hydric
<hw>Hy"dric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Hydrogen</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
containing, hydrogen; <as>as, <ex>hydric</ex> oxide</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hydric dioxide</b></col>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>See
